## 📡 Blynk Virtual Pins

| Pin | Data Type | Range | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| V0 | Integer | 0 / 1 | Motion indicator LED widget |
| V1 | String | — | Motion status text label |
| V2 | Integer | 0 / 1 | Alarm ON / OFF switch button |
| V3 | Double | 0–100 | ESP32 chip temperature (°C) |
| V4 | Integer | 0 / 1 | ESP32 online/offline status |
| V5 | String | — | ESP32 uptime (HH:MM:SS) |

> **ℹ️ Note on V3 Temperature**  
> V3 reads **chip die temperature**, not room temperature. A reading of **45–65°C is completely normal**. The chip runs 10–20°C hotter than ambient air. Only be concerned if it exceeds **80°C**.

