## 📶 WiFi Setup

Update your credentials in `SecurityAlarm.ino` before uploading:

```cpp
// Blynk Credentials
#define BLYNK_TEMPLATE_ID  "YOUR_TEMPLATE_ID"
#define BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN   "YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN_HERE"

// Primary WiFi
const char* WIFI_SSID1 = "YOUR_WIFI_NAME";
const char* WIFI_PASS1 = "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD";

// Backup WiFi (e.g. mobile hotspot)
const char* WIFI_SSID2 = "YOUR_BACKUP_WIFI_NAME";
const char* WIFI_PASS2 = "YOUR_BACKUP_PASSWORD";
```

> ⚠️ **Never commit real credentials to a public repository.** Always use placeholder text as shown above.

### 🔄 Auto Fallback Logic

If the primary network is unavailable, the ESP32 switches automatically:

```
Boot
 │
 ├─ Try WIFI_SSID1 ──── success ──► Connect & run normally
 │        │
 │      8 sec timeout
 │        │
 ├─ Try WIFI_SSID2 ──── success ──► Connect & run normally
 │        │
 │      8 sec timeout
 │        │
 └─ Offline Mode ──────────────► Retry every 20 seconds
```

> 💡 **Tip:** Set `WIFI_SSID2` to your **mobile hotspot**. If your router goes down, just enable your hotspot and the ESP32 reconnects within 8 seconds.

