## 📴 Offline Mode

The alarm works **without internet**. Here's exactly what happens:

| Scenario | Relay / Buzzer | Blynk Dashboard |
|---|---|---|
| WiFi connected, alarm ON | ✅ Triggers on motion | Notification + LED + label update |
| WiFi lost mid-session, alarm ON | ✅ Still triggers | Shows device offline |
| No WiFi at all, alarm ON | ✅ Still triggers | No update (no connection) |
| WiFi reconnects | ✅ Continues normally | State restored via `syncVirtual(V2)` |

> **How it works in code:**  
> The relay is driven by `setAlarmOutput()` which calls `digitalWrite(PIN_RELAY, HIGH)` regardless of WiFi state. All `Blynk.virtualWrite()` calls are wrapped in `if (Blynk.connected())` — they're simply skipped when offline. **The physical alarm always works.**

