## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Arduino IDE 2.x](https://arduino.cc/en/software)
- ESP32 board support — add this URL in **File > Preferences > Additional Board Manager URLs**:
  ```
  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
  ```
  Then install **esp32 by Espressif Systems** via **Tools > Board > Boards Manager**
- **Blynk library** — install via **Sketch > Include Library > Manage Libraries** → search `Blynk`
- A free account at [blynk.cloud](https://blynk.cloud)

### Installation

**1. Clone the repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Talha2933/ESP32-Security-Alarm.git
cd ESP32-Security-Alarm
```

**2. Set up Blynk** *(blynk.cloud)*
- Create a new Template: Hardware = ESP32, Connection = WiFi
- Add datastreams for V0, V1, V2, V3, V4, V5 (see [Virtual Pins](#-blynk-virtual-pins))
- Create event: code = `motion_detected`, Type = Critical, enable push + email
- Copy your **Template ID** and **Auth Token**

**3. Configure credentials**  
Open `SecurityAlarm.ino` and fill in your Blynk credentials and WiFi details (see [WiFi Setup](#-wifi-setup))

**4. Upload**
- Connect ESP32 via USB
- Select board: **Tools > Board > ESP32 Dev Module**
- Select port: **Tools > Port**
- Click **Upload** (`Ctrl+U`)
- Open Serial Monitor at `115200` baud — you should see `Blynk ONLINE`

**5. Test**
1. Open the Blynk app and turn the **Alarm Switch ON**
2. Wait **5 seconds** (PIR warm-up delay)
3. Walk past the sensor
4. The relay should trigger and a push notification should arrive on your phone
5. Try turning off your router — the relay should **still** fire on motion ✅

