## 🛠️ Troubleshooting

| Problem | Solution |
|---|---|
| Blynk shows device offline even when ESP is running | Normal behaviour when WiFi disconnects. `BLYNK_DISCONNECTED()` sends V4=0 before socket closes. Check your router. |
| Temperature reads 53°C at rest | Normal — chip die temperature runs 10–20°C above room temp. Not a fault. |
| No push notification received | Ensure the event code in Blynk is exactly `motion_detected` (lowercase, underscore). Enable notifications in Blynk app settings. |
| PIR triggers immediately when alarm turns ON | Increase `PIR_IGNORE_MS` to `8000` or `10000` in the code to extend the warm-up delay. |
| WiFi 2 not connecting | Check `WIFI_SSID2` / `WIFI_PASS2` — SSID is case-sensitive. Ensure DHCP is enabled on that network. |
| COM port not visible in Arduino IDE | Install the **CP2102** or **CH340** USB driver for your board. Search for your board model + "USB driver". |
| Upload fails with 'Failed to connect' | Hold the **BOOT** button on ESP32 while clicking Upload. Release after seeing `Connecting...` in the IDE. |

