## ⚠️ Security Warning

> **Never upload real credentials to a public repository.**  
> Your `BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN` and WiFi passwords must be replaced with placeholder text before committing to GitHub. Anyone with your Auth Token can control your device remotely.

Consider using a `secrets.h` file added to `.gitignore` for managing credentials safely:

```cpp
// secrets.h  ← add this filename to .gitignore
#define BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN   "your_real_token_here"
#define WIFI_SSID1         "your_real_ssid"
#define WIFI_PASS1         "your_real_password"
```

